 "RPS1 - not against edge" (Oct 19,  5:05pm)

On Oct 19,  5:05pm, Atom Smasher wrote:
}
} on a few different versions of zsh and a few different TERMs (though i 
} can't say i've tested thoroughly) it seems that the RPS1 (and also RPS2) 
} leave a single space between the prompt and the right edge of the 
} terminal. why is that?

To prevent the terminal from auto-scrolling and moving the prompt one
line up from the bottom.

